Why this numbness inducing - especially from the neck up - video was in my recommended, I'll never know. But since it was a curmudgeonly compulsion impelled me to comment.

The sheer goofiness and utter vapidity of what x, y z, w, v generations etc, ad nauseam, find entertaining is an ongoing source of bafflement to older folks. To have over 3 million subscribers with the total views in the who cares how many millions is suckingly stupid. And I don't mean that in a good way.

I don't fault the young lady that produces this dreck as much I do you millions of knuckleheads who suck down the drivel by the bucket fulls. How many 11:49 do you waste on vids like these? Or do you multitask by watching several different ones at a time on multiple devices? Maybe while doing your 4th grade homework new math? Now that, having watched a couple of so called educators explaining it, might just be a good idea.

Speaking as the grandfather you don't have or want, stop investing your time and mental energy on the fetid effluence of modern media. You'll end up stone cold broke pulling fuzz out of your navel. Of course then again maybe that's your goal to begin with.
